<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code assigns a user-supplied lookahead_buffer (cfg->lookahead_buffer) directly to lfs->lookahead.buffer without validating that the provided buffer is at least cfg->lookahead_size bytes. Later code may call standard library functions (e.g. memset/memcpy or other string.h functions) using lfs->lookahead.buffer together with cfg->lookahead_size. If the user-supplied buffer is smaller than cfg->lookahead_size, those calls would access beyond the bounds of the object and violate MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>

